{"key":"post-10009250","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>10009250</id>\n<content>Oyster mushrooms are probably the fastest growing mushrooms from inoculation to fruiting.&amp;nbsp; If your friend has oyster spawn, get that instead of spores.&amp;nbsp; It will be much faster.&amp;nbsp; In fact, tell him you want to grow mushrooms in an old shoe, and he'll probably give you what you need.&amp;nbsp; You'll want to boil the shoe in water to kill off the molds, and then fill it up with the sawdust spawn he gives you.&amp;nbsp; Keep it loosely wrapped in plastic until fully colonized, and then set it outside in a shady spot, especially if it's the rainy season, which I'm pretty sure it is in Holland.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Here's an art project for ya!&lt;br /&gt;RR&lt;br /&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://files.shroomery.org/files/07-26/327075751-Gay_bra_pic.jpg&quot; class=&quot;highslide&quot; onclick=&quot;return hs.expand(this,{slideshowGroup:'hsg1'})&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/thumbs/07-26/327075751-thumb_Gay_bra_pic.jpg&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>10010273</next>\n<prev>10008997</prev>\n<first>10003682</first>\n<last>10010273</last>\n<when>1237591058</when>\n<utime>03/21/09 02:17 AM</utime>\n</post>"}